<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-86-0916 </DOCNO><TEXT>Combined calibration of 3 whole-body spectrometers of various design andmeasurement of potassium in the group of persons were performed. Causesof divergence were analysed and readings of instruments within +- 5%were summarized. The importance of choice of a calibration phantom whichwas radiometrically adequate to the human body and a necessity of establishingcorrelations between phantom parameters and anthropometric data on manwere shown.</TEXT></DOC>